<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=240476#M240476">101</a> of 165
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 975 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Yes I have the cloak on a level 60 character.&nbsp; No, I wasnt complaining about it.&nbsp; I was pointing out the difference of before and after the patch.&nbsp; The cloak takes 5x longer even with the supposed modification to the way the evolving item gains XP.&nbsp; Heck, I am tickled pink to have the level 1 version so if I misconstrued general information about how long it takes to level as complaints than that was my error.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As further proof the cloak takes 5x longer to evolve it appears that every single cloak that wasnt level 3&nbsp;has been reduced to under 40% of level 1.&nbsp; 40% x 5 = 200% which would be 2 dings and a level 3 cloak.&nbsp; Sadly to say, the modifications made to the cloak have made the evolving item changes invisible in regards to that one.&nbsp; Now, people with the Skull of Den Lord Rakban and other evolving items are reporting significant increases in the speed at which&nbsp;the item evolves.&nbsp; So they did work, its just difficult to see on the Cloak because that was also changed to require more XP.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>06-14-2006</span> <span class=time_text>10:13 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
