<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=240765#M240765">109</a> of 165
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 773 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I swear, this is getting out of hand.&nbsp; I think the word "casual" should be banned as it is the most abused term on this messageboard.&nbsp; "SoE hates casuals" is practically code for "I don't want obstacles to over come" or "this game is too hard for me".&nbsp; I probably spend less time in game per week than most of the extremely skewed non-raiders.&nbsp; There are many non-raiders on these boards who not only understand the mechanics and concepts of the game, but when presented with an obstacle, they have the mental fortitude as well as the charisma to persevere.&nbsp; To those folks I applaud you as you have constructed for yourselves an environment of fun with what it available in the game.&nbsp; And of course there are those that want EQ to become WoWthatwasfast.&nbsp; EQ is not that other game.&nbsp; I hope it never becomes WoWfullofbattlenetkiddies.&nbsp; EQ was designed freeform and allowed us, the players, to decide our own fates or our own ways of combatting obstacles.&nbsp; For the raiding community it is overcoming that difficult series of raid encounters.&nbsp; For the community that does not raid as much or not at all, it is about grouping with your friends and embarking on great adventures (this is where I fit in).&nbsp; And who benefits the most in EQ legitimately?&nbsp; Those who are good at making large numbers of friends.&nbsp; It's amazing how many friendships are built from a "hey bro, how you doing today?" or a "safe hunting to you."&nbsp; The fun of EQ, no matter if it is raid or non-raid is banding together and overcoming whatever obstacle is in the way.&nbsp; I would probably not be playing EQ at all if not for my friends.&nbsp; <br><br>If I want to solo, I have an Xbox and playstation to cover that.&nbsp; Half the fun for me in EQ is just sitting around in guild hall and shooting the breeze with friends in chat.&nbsp; It's the built friendships that keep most of us in an archaic game like EQ and it's these great friends that keep us moving forward from whatever point we are at.<br><br>There are real problems out there like the stupid west bug, the channeling issue, class imbalance, macroquesters and some zones screwed up just to name a few.&nbsp; But the codephrase "SoE hates casuals" a.k.a. I lost the option for "easy" in my options window is way too abused.<br><br>Flame on! I'm getting the marshmallows <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><br><div></div>	
		</td></tr>
