<DIV>The cloak doesnt "appear" to have the grouping/even con/faster leveling benefit to it because it was the only item that had its required XP increased.&nbsp; For all we know, the cloak may have had its required XP increased by 10x but the other benefits have reduced it to an effective 5x which is what we now see.&nbsp; You can't tell because two variables changed.&nbsp; What we know is Required XP increase minus Grouping/Even con/"Way evolving items receive XP" = 5x difference from last time.&nbsp; At least from a soloing perspective.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I didnt test the cloak before doing the white con&nbsp;Shiknar&nbsp;in the back of Fungus Grove(as I didnt realize the cloak was going to be changed) so I dont know what gained 1% in a group then.&nbsp; I do know that before the initial cloak XP increase that happened at the same time as the quest change I was leveling it on my monk and 2 dk blue kills in The HOle at lvel 70&nbsp; got 1% in a 2 man group. 1 kill there solo got 1% on cloak.&nbsp; In FG, 70 monk grouped with 60 char got no increase in 12 shrooms before this recent patch(and it seemed as it got nothing -not even partial gains that might have eventually added up to 1% becuase when I went back to solo with 60 char it took 2 kills to get to the next percent).</DIV>	
