			<blockquote><hr>Rashere wrote:<br>
<div>&nbsp;<br>
In an effort to improve the overall time it takes to evolve all items,
with this patch we significantly improved the amount of experience you
gain toward an evolving item&nbsp;when you get a kill.&nbsp; This in
turn&nbsp;caused the Cloak to&nbsp; level up way too fast.&nbsp; To
correct this, we had to increase the amount of experience the Cloak
requires to level so it is more in line with other evolving items,
which should now level up at a much more appropriate rate.<br>
</div><hr></blockquote>This being the case, you grossly missed the
mark.&nbsp; Whereas I could get 1% evolution from a couple dark blue
solo kills prior to the nerf, an entire group burning through a hive
mission and killing reds and yellows netted me 5% evolution in about 90
minutes.&nbsp; My previous rate was 25% per hour, solo.&nbsp; The
adjustments made to this item have not only annoyed a good deal of
customers; they have also overshot the <i>correction</i> to the Cloak's rate of evolution which was meant to offset patch changes.<br>
