<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=241575#M241575">125</a> of 165
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 412 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>Just two things:</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>To level the cloak to max you have to "ding" it 2 times.<BR>To level the Blade of the Night Sky to max you have to "ding" it 6 times.</P>
<P>So far both items gained XP on the same rate, i.e. to have the blade at max you needed 3 times longer (to ding 3 times as much).</P>
<P>With the change the XP gain on the cloak was reduced to 1/5th (mine went from level 2/0% to level 1/20%), so to evolve the cloak to max now actually takes a significantly longer time than to evolve a Blade of the Night Sky to max.<BR>To give a number: Seeing that so far 4ish mobs in GE gave 1% we are now talking about 20ish mobs / % or 4,000 mobs total to get the cloak to level 3 (you'll know where to find me the next&nbsp;2 years. In comparison, the Blade of the Night Sky to full takes 2,400 mobs.</P>
<P>To the devs: Please keep in mind that the number of complaints in this thread will be lower since cloaks at level 2 were devolved to level 1/20%, but most cloaks at level 3 stayed there, which eliminates a lot of complaints. Once again I'm angry on myself that I don't belong to the "early adaptors".</P>
<P>Suggestion: Bring the evolving rate in line with the Blade of the Night Sky (i.e. increase the required XP by 3 not by 5).</P>
<P>It was an obvious mistake to devolve some cloaks while leaving others as they were, but since I don't believe that it will be rolled back, I just ask that you *please* do *not touch* the cloaks that you haven't devolved. While it's not fair, it's at least something good for a good number of players. And of course - I don't need more competition in GE when I go kill my 3,600 mobs.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>	
		</td></tr>
